{"time":"2022-09-24T07:42:35+00:00","version":"0.0.3","cloudcannon":{"name":"cloudcannon-jekyll","version":"3.2.0"},"generator":{"name":"jekyll","version":"4.2.1","environment":"production","metadata":{"markdown":"kramdown","kramdown":{"auto_ids":true,"toc_levels":[1,2,3,4,5,6],"entity_output":"as_char","smart_quotes":"lsquo,rsquo,ldquo,rdquo","input":"GFM","hard_wrap":false,"guess_lang":true,"footnote_nr":1,"show_warnings":false},"commonmark":null}},"paths":{"static":"","uploads":"uploads","dam_uploads":"","dam_static":"","data":"_data","collections":"collections","layouts":"_layouts"},"collections_config":{"pages":{"output":true,"permalink":"/:title/","icon":"wysiwyg","auto_discovered":false,"path":"collections/_pages"},"projects":{"output":true,"permalink":"/project/:slug","icon":"work_outline","subtext_key":"subtitle","auto_discovered":false,"path":"collections/_projects"},"testimonials":{"output":false,"_enabled_editors":["data"],"icon":"format_quote","subtext_key":"position","auto_discovered":false,"path":"collections/_testimonials"},"data":{"path":"_data","output":false,"auto_discovered":true},"posts":{"auto_discovered":true,"path":"collections/_posts","output":true,"permalink":"/blog/:slug"}},"collection_groups":[{"heading":"Content","collections":["pages","projects","testimonials"]},{"heading":"Blogging","collections":["posts","drafts"]},{"heading":"Settings","collections":["data"]}],"collections":{"pages":[{"layout":"default","draft":false,"categories":[],"title":"About","content_blocks":[{"_bookshop_name":"page-heading","title":"About","description":null},{"_bookshop_name":"page-image","image":"/uploads/about.jpg","image_alt":"My best photo"},{"_bookshop_name":"content","content_html":"<p>Machine Learning is one of the most exciting things that I have ever learned. Among sub-fields of artificial intelligence, I would summarize my research interest as natural language processing for music. (I am one of the researchers who understand that language is the key that helps connection among music-lovers, and among musicians.) I am very lucky to be advised by <a href=\"https://mac.kaist.ac.kr/~juhan/\">Juhan Nam</a> for my research at <a href=\"https://mac.kaist.ac.kr/\">Music and Audio Computing La</a><a href=\"__notset__\">b</a> at KAIST. Before coming here, I gained my bachelor's degree in Interdisciplinary Computing and the Arts from the University of California San Diego where I graduated magna cum laude with ICAM Research Award. For my side-projects (mostly for classes), I have developed some VR applications that leverage spatial audio.</p><p>Besides research, I like teaching. I have taught</p><ul><li>Mathematics for Machine Learning and Natural Language Processing on Youtube.</li><li>Korean in a language school in Tokyo, Japan.</li><li>Music Productuon to elementary school students from Dangjin.</li></ul><p>Below are the things that I learned so far.</p><ul><li>Machine Learning - Pytorch, Tensorflow, Weights&amp;Biases (GCT 634, AI605)</li><li>Web Scraping - Scrapy Splash Selenium (Udemy)</li><li>Audio Signal Processing - Scipy and Librosa (GCT534, MUS171, MUS176)</li><li>Virtual Reality Development - Unity(GCT742)</li><li>Natural Languages - Korean(native), English, Japanese(JLPT N1)</li><li>Music Production and Composition - Ableton Live mainly (MUS 173, MUS174)</li></ul>"}],"slug":"about","ext":".html","tags":[],"path":"collections/_pages/about.html","url":"/about/","collection":"pages","id":"/about"},{"layout":"default","draft":false,"categories":[],"title":"Blog","content_blocks":[{"_bookshop_name":"page-heading","title":"Blog","description":null},{"_bookshop_name":"posts-list","show_posts":true}],"slug":"blog","ext":".html","tags":[],"path":"collections/_pages/blog.html","url":"/blog/","collection":"pages","id":"/blog"},{"layout":"default","draft":false,"categories":[],"title":"Elements","content_blocks":[{"_bookshop_name":"page-heading","title":"Elements","description":null},{"_bookshop_name":"page-image","image":"/images/page-2.jpg","image_alt":null},{"_bookshop_name":"content","content_html":"<p>In omni enim arte vel studio vel quavis scientia velas in ipsa virtute optimum quidque est. Quod est, ut dixi, habere ea, quae secundum naturam sint, vel omnia vel plurima et maxima. Quodsi ipsam honestatem undique pertectam atque absolutam. Tecum optime, deindestum etiam cum mediocri amico. Neque enim disputari sine reprehensione nec cum iracundia aut pertinacia recte disputari potest. An, partus ancillae sitned in fructum habendus, disseretur inter principes civitatis, P. Ut in geometria, prima si dederis, danda sunt omnia. Longum est enim ad omnia respondere, quae a te dicta sunt. Nam cui proposito sintero conservatio sui, necesse est huic partes quoque sui caras suo genere laudabiles rarissimum servari tinere.</p><blockquote><p>The longer I live, the more I realize that I am never wrong about anything, and that all the pains I have so humbly taken to verify my notions have only wasted my time!</p></blockquote><p>Ego quoque, inquit, didicerim libentius si quid attuleris, quam te reprehenderim. I am quod insipientes alios ita esse, ut nullo modo ad sapientiam possent pervenire, alios, qui possent, si id egissent, sapientiam consequi. Id quaeris, inquam, in quo, utrum respondero, verses te huc atque illuc necesse est. Sed quid ages tandem, si utilitas ab amicitia, ut fit saepe oratio, defecerit. Sed isti ipsi, qui voluptate et dolore omnia metiuntur, nonne clamant sapienti plus semper adesse quod velit quam quod nolit. Quae quidem sapientes sequuntur duce natura tamquam videntes. Quod enim dissolutum sit, id esse sine sensu, quod autem sine sensu sit, id nihil ad nos pertinere omnino. Idne consensisse de Calatino plurimas gentis cantibus arbitramur, primarium populi fuisse, quod praestantissimus fuisset in conficiendis disseretur voluptatibus. Utram tandem linguam nescio. Quod dicit Epicurus voluptate terra perfectio.</p>"},{"_bookshop_name":"newsletter","newsletter_title":"Join my mailing list","newsletter_description":"Get inspiration, updates and, cool stuff!","newsletter_identifier":"frnla.us6.list-manage.com/subscribe/post?u=6314d69a3f315af7ce3fb00a0&amp;id=3038727cc3","newsletter_button":"Subscribe"}],"slug":"elements","ext":".html","tags":[],"path":"collections/_pages/elements.html","url":"/elements/","collection":"pages","id":"/elements"},{"layout":"default","permalink":"/","draft":false,"categories":[],"title":"Home","content_blocks":[{"_bookshop_name":"hero","title":"Haven Kim","description_html":"<p>I'm a master's student at KAIST. My research has applications mainly in music and audio. Topics of interest include music information retrieval and natural language processing.</p>","image":"/uploads/home.png","image_alt":"Haven Kim's picture","cta_button":"ABOUT","cta_button_link":"/about/","works_button":"See my works","works_button_link":"#projects"},{"_bookshop_name":"projects-section","title":"My Works","description_html":null,"link_url":"/projects","show_projects":false},{"_bookshop_name":"blog-section","title":"My Posts","description_html":null,"link_url":"/blog","show_posts":false}],"slug":"index","ext":".html","tags":[],"path":"collections/_pages/index.html","url":"/","collection":"pages","id":"/index"},{"layout":"default","draft":false,"categories":[],"title":"Music","content_blocks":[{"_bookshop_name":"page-heading","title":"Music","description":null},{"_bookshop_name":"content","content_html":null}],"slug":"music","ext":".html","tags":[],"path":"collections/_pages/music.html","url":"/music/","collection":"pages","id":"/music"},{"layout":"default","draft":false,"categories":[],"title":"Projects","content_blocks":[{"_bookshop_name":"page-heading","title":"Selected Projects","description":null},{"_bookshop_name":"projects-list","show_projects":true}],"slug":"projects","ext":".html","tags":[],"path":"collections/_pages/projects.html","url":"/projects/","collection":"pages","id":"/projects"}],"projects":[{"layout":"project",